data.title: Morgan Wallen Teases New Track and It's Sooo Different
data.meta_description: Morgan Wallen captivates fans with a tantalizing snippet of his upcoming music, blending a melodic guitar riff with enchanting harmonies. The country star's unexpected high notes leave listeners in awe, sparking anticipation for his upcoming album.
data.text:
Morgan Wallen has been keeping fans on the edge of their seat when it comes to new music, and he's finally pulling back the curtain. After sharing photos from the studio, the country singer is teasing a new track on social media.

And, it's unlike anything he's done before.

The untitled song features a simple guitar line and an ethereal chorus of voices carrying him through the lyrics. Just when you think you know where he's headed, Wallen belts out some unexpected high notes.

Take a listen below, and keep scrolling to see fan reactions and the lyrics.

Fans and Fellow Artists Are Loving Morgan Wallen's New Music

Wallen has yet to reveal details about the new track, but fans and fellow artists are flooding the comments with praise.

"Gosh nobody is as good as you," Anne Wilson writes while Travis Denning chimes in with "Good Lawd."

"THIS THAT S--T," Bailey Zimmerman types.

"This next album is gonna be so special," one fan shares.

"Chill song with fire potential," another comments. "I’m here for it!"

Here Are the Lyrics to Morgan Wallen's New Song

I can’t remember / The last time / You looked as happy, as you did tonight / You’re tipsy friend, grabbed that bartender / Gave him her phone, and pulled us over there with her / He counted to three, baby I haven’t seen / This side of you in forever

I hate that’s the truth but baby you never do when we’re alone together / But it was good to see you smile / Girl you know it's been awhile / It was good to see you smile, even if it was just for the picture

Jess hosts the syndicated radio show, Taste of Country Weekend, which can be heard on country stations nationwide. Tune in for all of the best new country music, spotlights on new tracks and emerging artists, plus Double-Downs on all of your favorites. The weekend is always better with a little Taste of Country in it.
